name: Jared Isaacman
summary: President Trump has selected Jared Isaacman, a billionaire astronaut and founder of the private space company SpaceX, to lead NASA. Mr. Isaacman has extensive experience in commercial spaceflight, having previously completed a private spacewalk and visited the International Space Station. His appointment has been met with mixed reactions, with some praising his expertise and others expressing concerns about his lack of government experience. If confirmed by the Senate, Mr. Isaacman would become the first private citizen to lead NASA.

name: Chad Chronister
summary: Chad Chronister, a Florida sheriff chosen by President Trump to lead the Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA), has withdrawn his name from consideration. Trump initially claimed that he had "pulled" Chronister from the nomination due to the sheriff's involvement in the arrest of a pastor. However, Chronister later stated that he had withdrawn himself, contradicting Trump's version of events. Chronister's nomination had been met with bipartisan criticism due to concerns about his lack of experience in federal law enforcement and his previous support for controversial policies. The withdrawal marks a setback for Trump's administration and leaves the DEA administrator position vacant.

name: XDefiant
summary: Ubisoft's free-to-play shooter, XDefiant, is coming to an end. Ubisoft has discontinued development and will shut down the game in June 2025. This decision is part of a larger restructuring at Ubisoft, which includes studio closures and layoffs affecting nearly 300 employees. Affected players will receive refunds, and in-game changes are already being implemented. The closure of XDefiant marks another setback for Ubisoft, which has faced numerous challenges in recent years, including multiple delays and cancellations.
